      • registerAtomicallyTaggableClass

        public static void registerAtomicallyTaggableClass(java.lang.Class cls)
        If an object is tagged that is NOT an instanceof any of the classes that have been registered as atomically taggable, then the change is in limbo, and the effigy of the Kepler graph is explicitly set as changed to force a save dialog on closing. For example, tagging a workflow adds a semantic type that is rendered to MOML when the workflow is saved. This is not an atomic change. On the other hand, tagging a workflow run immediately adds the tag to the REAP database, so this is atomic.
        Parameters:
        cls - Class to register
